msgid:
If your TV has a brightness or contrast enhancement, disable it. If there is something called "dynamic", set it to standard. Adjust the backlight level to a value suiting your taste. Turn down contrast on your TV as much as possible.
Then turn the brightness setting as low as possible, but make sure that the two lowermost shades of gray stay distinguishable.
Do not care about the bright shades now. They will be set up in the next step.
If you are happy with the result, press OK.
openatv:
Om din TV har ljusstyrke- eller kontrastförbättrare, stänga av den. Om det finns något som heter "dynamic", använd standard. Justera ljusstyrkan till en inställning som du tycker är bra. Använd så lite kontrast som möjligt.
Sätt ljusstyrkan till så låg som möjligt, men säkerställ att de två lägsta nivåerna av grå är urskiljningsbara.
Ta inte hänsyn till de ljusa nivåerna nu. De kommer justeras i nästa steg.
När du är nöjd med resultatet, tryck OK.
openhdf:

Select 'FBC SCR' if this tuner will connect to a SCR (Unicable/JESS) device. For all other setups select 'FBC automatic'.
Select 'Yes' when you want to configure this tuner for ATSC
Select 'Yes' when you want to configure this tuner for DVB-C
Select 'Yes' when you want to configure this tuner for DVB-S
Select 'Yes' when you want to configure this tuner for DVB-T
Select 'band' if using a 'universal' LNB, otherwise consult your LNB spec sheet.
Select 'enabled' if this tuner has a signal cable connected, otherwise select 'nothing connected'.
Select 'polarisation' if using a 'universal' LNB, otherwise consult your LNB spec sheet.

Select 'provider' to scan from the predefined list of cable multiplexes. Select 'bands' to only scan certain parts of the spectrum. Select 'steps' to scan in steps of a particular frequency bandwidth.
Select 'yes' if this tuner is connected to the SCR device through another tuner, otherwise select 'no'.
Select 'yes' to choose what bands or step sizes will be scanned.
Select 'yes' to include %s multiplexes in your search.
Select 'yes' to include symbol rate %s in your search.
Select 'yes' to include the %s band in your search.
Select 'yes' to only send the DiSEqC command when changing from one satellite to another, or select 'no' for the DiSEqC command to be resent on every zap.

msgid: Select how quickly the dish should move between satellites.
Select how the satellite dish is set up. i.e. fixed dish, single LNB, DiSEqC switch, positioner, etc.
Select the User Band channel to be assigned to this tuner. This is an index into the table of frequencies the SCR switch or SCR LNB uses to pass the requested transponder to the tuner.
Select the User Band frequency to be assigned to this tuner. This is the frequency the SCR switch or SCR LNB uses to pass the requested transponder to the tuner.
Select the User Band to be assigned to this tuner. This is an index into the table of frequencies the SCR switch or SCR LNB uses to pass the requested transponder to the tuner.

Select the protocol used by your SCR device. Choices are 'SCR Unicable' (Unicable), or 'SCR JESS' (JESS, also known as Unicable II).

Select the satellite which is connected to Port-A of your switch. If you are unsure select 'automatic' and the receiver will attempt to determine this for you. If nothing is connected to this port, select 'nothing connected'.

Select the satellite which is connected to Port-B of your switch. If you are unsure select 'automatic' and the receiver will attempt to determine this for you. If nothing is connected to this port, select 'nothing connected'.

Select the satellite which is connected to Port-C of your switch. If you are unsure select 'automatic' and the receiver will attempt to determine this for you. If nothing is connected to this port, select 'nothing connected'.

Select the satellite which is connected to Port-D of your switch. If you are unsure select 'automatic' and the receiver will attempt to determine this for you. If nothing is connected to this port, select 'nothing connected'.
Select the satellite you want to configure. Once that satellite is configured you can select and configure other satellites that will be accessed using this same tuner.
Select the satellite your dish receives from. If you are unsure select 'automatic' and the receiver will attempt to determine this for you.

Select the tuner that controls the motorised dish.

msgid: This setting allows the tuner configuration to be a duplication of how another tuner is already configured.

This test checks for configured nameservers.
If you get a "unconfirmed" message:
- please check your DHCP, cabling and adapter setup
- if you configured your nameservers manually please verify your entries in the "Nameserver" configuration

Detta test söker efter konfigurerade namnservrar.
Om du får ett "obekräftad" meddelande:
- vänligen kontrollera din DHCP, kablar och adapterinställning

msgid: Warning: no LNB; using factory defaults.

Welcome to the cutlist editor.

Seek to the start of the stuff you want to cut away. Press OK, select 'start cut'.

Then seek to the end, press OK, select 'end cut'. That's it.

Sök början på det innehåll du vill klippa bort. Tryck OK, välj 'start cut'.

Sök därefter slutet på det innehåll du vill klippa bort, tryck OK, välj 'end cut'. Det var allt.
openhdf:
Välkommen till Cutlist editor.

Sök början på det innehåll du vill klippa bort. Tryck OK, välj 'start cut'.

Sök därefter slutet på det innehåll du vill klippa bort, tryck OK, välj 'end cut'. Det var allt.
openpli:
Välkommen till klippeditorn.

Sök början på det innehåll du vill klippa bort. Tryck OK, välj 'startklipp'.

Sök därefter slutet på det innehåll du vill klippa bort, tryck OK, välj 'slutklipp'. Det var allt.
openvix:
Välkommen till Cutlist editor.

Sök början på det innehåll du vill klippa bort. Tryck OK, välj 'start cut'.

Sök därefter slutet på det innehåll du vill klippa bort, tryck OK, välj 'end cut'. Det var allt.

msgid:
Welcome.

If you want to connect your receiver to the Internet, this wizard will guide you through the basic network setup of your receiver.

Press OK to start configuring your network
openpli:
Välkommen.

Om du vill ansluta din mottagare till Internet, då kommer den här guiden hjälpa dig genom grundläggande konfiguration av din mottagare.

Tryck OK för att starta konfigurationen av ditt nätverk

msgid:
Welcome.

This start wizard will guide you through the basic setup of your receiver.
Press the OK button on your remote control to move to the next step.
openpli:
Välkommen.

Den här guiden hjälper dig med grundinställningarna av din mottagare.
Tryck OK på din fjärrkontroll för att komma till nästa steg.

msgid: What type of service scan do you want?

When enabled enigma2 will load unlinked userbouquets. This means that userbouquets that are available, but not included in the bouquets.tv or bouquets.radio files, will still be loaded. This allows you for example to keep your own user bouquet while installed settings are updated
openpli: Vid aktiverad laddar enigma2 olänkade favoritlistor. Detta innebär att favoritlistor som är tillgängliga men som inte ingår i bouquet.tv eller bouquet.radio filer kommer fortfarande laddas. Detta gör att du till exempel kan behålla dina egna favoritlistor medan installerade inställningar uppdateras.

msgid: When enabled the Picture in Picture window can be closed with 'exit' button.
openpli: Vid aktiverad kan BiB stängas med exitknappen.

msgid: When enabled the arrow buttons around the OK button will follow the 'neutrino' style zap controls instead of the enigma2 style.

msgid: When enabled the set top box is able to wakeup on LAN

msgid: When enabled the timer from the fallback tuner is imported

msgid: When enabled you can customize the OpenWebIf settings for the fallback tuner

msgid:
You did not see all eight arrow heads. This means your TV has overscan enabled and presents you with a zoomed-in picture, causing you to loose part of a full HD screen. In addition this you may also miss parts of the user interface, for example volume bars and more.

Unfortunately, your model of receiver is not capable to adjust the dimensions of the user interface. If not everything is visible, you should change the installed skin to one that supports the overscan area of your TV.

When you select a different skin, the user interface of your receiver will restart.

Note: you can always start the Overscan wizard later,  via

menu->installation->system->Overscan wizard
openpli:
Du såg inte alla åtta pilhuvudena. Din TV har överskanning aktiverat och visar dig en inzoomad bild, det gör att du mister en del av HD bilden. Det gör också att du mister delar av användargränssnittet, till exempel volymfältet m.m.

Tyvärr så klarar inte din mottagare av att justera dimensionerna på användargränssnittet. Om inte allt är synlig, bör du ändra det installerade utseendet till ett som stöder överskanningsområdet på din TV.

När du väljer ett annat utseende, kommer användargränssnittet för din mottagare att starta om.

Notera : du kan alltid starta överskanningsguiden senare, via

meny->installation->system->överskanningsguide

msgid:
This test checks whether your LAN adapter is set up for automatic IP address configuration with DHCP.
If you get a "disabled" message:
 - then your LAN adapter is configured for manual IP setup
- verify thay you have entered correct IP informations in the adapter setup dialog.
If you get an "enabled" message:
-verify that you have a configured and working DHCP server in your network.
openatv:
Detta test kontrollerar om din LAN-adapter är inställd för automatisk tilldelning av IP-adress med DHCP.
Om du får ett "avaktiverad"meddelande:
- då är din LAN-adapter konfigurerad för manuell IP-tilldelning
-verifiera att du har matat in korrekt IP-information i adapterns inställningar.
Om du får ett "aktiverad"meddelande:
-verifiera att du har en konfigurerad och fungerande DHCP-server i ditt nätverk.
openhdf:
Detta test kontrollerar om din LAN-adapter är inställd för automatisk tilldelning av IP-adress med DHCP.

This plugin creates a USB stick which can be used to update the firmware of your %s %s without the need for a network or WLAN connection.

If you already have a prepared bootable USB stick, please insert it now. Otherwise plug in a USB stick with a minimum size of 64 MB!

Det här pluginet skapar en USB-sticka som kan användas för att uppdatera firmware i din %s %s utan behovet av nätverks- eller WLAN anslutning.

Nästa steg, en NFI image fil ska laddas ner från uppdateringsservern och sparas till USB stickan.
Om du redan har en förberedd bootbar USB sticka, vänligen sätt in den nu. Annars anslut en USB sticka med minimum 64 MB minne!

Select 'Yes' to remove all network data. Selecting this option will remove all network data including automounts and network connection data including connection accounts and passwords. This could cause some Enigma2 functions to fail if they are configured to use these network resources.
Select 'Yes' to remove all other files and directories not covered by the options above.

Select 'Yes' to remove all plugin configuration data. Selecting this option will remove all plugin configuration data that is stored in the Enigma2 configuration folder. This will cause all affected plugins to return to their default settings. This could cause some plugins to not function until configured.

Select 'Yes' to remove all settings, tuning data, timers, resume pointers etc. Selecting this option will restore the configuration to the initial settings before any configuration settings were applied. This is the most reliable form of Factory Reset.
Select 'Yes' to remove all timer configuration data. Selecting this option will clear all timers, autotimers and power timers.
Select 'Yes' to remove all tuning data. Selecting this option will remove all tuning and bouquet data and will make timers non functional until the receiver is retuned.

Select 'Yes' to remove all user customisations of skin data. Selecting this option will remove all user based skin customisations. All affected skins will return to their standard settings. This will also clear any customied boot logos and backdrops.
